fall_detection_transformer.tflite
=================================

Vendored, unmodified, from:
  https://github.com/punpayut/Fall-Detection
  (deployment/raspberry_pi/fall_detection_transformer.tflite)

The model is a Transformer trained on MediaPipe-Pose keypoint sequences
(30 frames x 51 features) and emits a single fall probability.

ZENTRA's backend/utils/fall_detector.py reproduces that project's feature
contract verbatim — the 17 keypoint names sorted alphabetically, the
[x, y, confidence] layout at [3i, 3i+1, 3i+2], and the hip-centred /
torso-scaled per-frame normalisation — so the weights see exactly the input
they were trained on. Verified element-wise against the upstream
implementation (max |diff| = 0.0).

Note: the shipped file is the 30-timestep model. The 94.9% F1 figure reported
in the upstream README belongs to a 60-timestep + augmentation model that is
not distributed.

